A vintage-style illustration of a frustrated taxi driver inside a classic yellow cab, viewed from the passenger's perspective. The driver's weathered hands hover over an overcomplicated dashboard console covered in unnecessary buttons, switches, and a glowing touchscreen displaying multiple confusing prompts. The cab interior has warm amber tones with worn leather seats and art deco design elements. Through the rain-streaked windows, the blurred neon lights of a bustling Asian cityscape create bokeh effects in deep blues and magentas. The driver's expression in the rearview mirror shows mild exasperation. A contactless payment card sits abandoned on the passenger seat, catching a single beam of streetlight. The overall mood evokes 1940s travel posters meets modern urban complexity, with muted sepia undertones contrasting against scattered pops of electric color from the dashboard display.
